- Use proper error handling: anticipate failure modes and handle them deliberately
- Prefer exceptions over error codes when the language/ecosystem supports it; don’t encode failure in magic return values
- Fail fast on invalid inputs (validate early) and surface actionable error messages
- Add context when propagating errors (what operation failed, key identifiers), but avoid leaking secrets
- Don’t swallow errors silently; handle, log, or rethrow as appropriate
- Use graceful degradation when possible; avoid hard crashes for recoverable errors
